<td class="mbox-text" style=""><span class="mbox-text-span">Constructs such as <i><a href="Ibid." title="Ibid.">ibid.</a></i>, <i><a href="Loc._cit." title="Loc. cit.">loc. cit.</a></i> and <i><a href="Idem" title="Idem">idem</a></i> are <b>discouraged by <a href="Wikipedia_Footnotes#Style_recommendations" title="Wikipedia:Footnotes" class="mw-redirect">Wikipedia's style guide</a> for footnotes</b>, as they are easily broken. Please <a class="external text" href="../../w/index-title=Bass_drum&action=edit.php.html">improve this article</a> by replacing them with <a href="Wikipedia_Footnotes#Naming_a_ref_tag_so_it_can_be_used_more_than_once" title="Wikipedia:Footnotes" class="mw-redirect">named references</a> (<i><a href="Template_Refref" title="Template:Refref">quick guide</a></i>), or an abbreviated title. <small><i>(March 2012)</i></small> </span></td>
</tr>
</table>
